line — full developer desktop with tools, theming, shell, and more.","title":"Quick Start","titles":["cattery"],"type":"section"},"2":{"category":"","href":"/#why-cattery","subtitle":"","text":" Room-based — pre-configured module bundles; enable one and get dozensSensible defaults — every module comes with good defaults, override what you needCross-platform — NixOS, nix-darwin, home-manager, and NixOS-WSLModular — use rooms for quick-start, or enable individual modules piece by pieceExtensible — compose rooms with extra modules from other flakes","title":"Why cattery?","titles":["cattery"],"type":"section"},"3":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#quick-start","subtitle":"","text":" Add cattery as a flake input: {\n  inputs = {\n    nixpkgs.url = \"github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable\";\n    cattery-modules.url = \"https://flakehub.com/f/nixcafe/cattery-modules/*.tar.gz\";\n  };\n}","title":"Quick Start","titles":[],"type":"page"},"4":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#installation","subtitle":"","text":" Add cattery as a flake input: {\n  inputs = {\n    nixpkgs.url = \"github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable\";\n    cattery-modules.url = \"https://flakehub.com/f/nixcafe/cattery-modules/*.tar.gz\";\n  };\n}","title":"Installation","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"5":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#enabling-a-room","subtitle":"","text":" Rooms are the fastest way to get started. Add the modules to your system config and enable a room: # configuration.nix\n{ cattery-modules, ... }: {\n  imports = [ cattery-modules.nixosModules.default ];\n\n  cattery.room.desktop.dev.enable = true;\n} That's it. Run nixos-rebuild switch and you'll have a fully configured developer desktop.","title":"Enabling a Room","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"6":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#using-with-home-manager","subtitle":"","text":" Standalone home-manager (no NixOS): # home.nix\n{ cattery-modules, ... }: {\n  imports = [ cattery-modules.homeModules.default ];\n\n  cattery.room.desktop.dev.enable = true;\n}","title":"Using with Home-Manager","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"7":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#using-with-nix-darwin","subtitle":"","text":" macOS users: { cattery-modules, ... }: {\n  imports = [ cattery-modules.darwinModules.default ];\n\n  cattery.room.desktop.dev.enable = true;\n}","title":"Using with nix-darwin","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"8":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#picking-individual-modules","subtitle":"","text":" Don't want a full room? Enable modules one at a time: {\n  cattery = {\n    themes.catppuccin.enable = true;\n    desktop.hyprland.enable = true;\n    services.tailscale.enable = true;\n    cli-apps.dev-kit.git.enable = true;\n  };\n}","title":"Picking Individual Modules","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"9":{"category":"","href":"/rooms#rooms","subtitle":"","text":" Rooms are pre-configured module bundles. Enable one room and get dozens of modules with sensible defaults. Each room includes and extends the one below it.","title":"Rooms","titles":[],"type":"page"},"10":{"category":"","href":"/rooms#room-hierarchy","subtitle":"","text":" room.basis\n └─ room.general\n     ├─ room.server-mini\n     │   └─ room.server\n     ├─ room.container\n     └─ room.desktop.basis\n          └─ room.desktop.general\n               ├─ room.desktop.dev\n               ├─ room.desktop.game\n               └─ room.desktop.wsl","title":"Room Hierarchy","titles":["Rooms"],"type":"section"},"11":{"category":"","href":"/rooms#base-rooms","subtitle":"","text":" RoomDescriptionKey Modulesroom.basisEssential system setupnix, git, openssh, locale, fonts, networkroom.generalEveryday additionsshell (fish/zsh), CLI tools, editors, file manager","title":"Base Rooms","titles":["Rooms","Available Rooms"],"type":"section"},"12":{"category":"","href":"/rooms#server-rooms","subtitle":"","text":" RoomDescriptionKey Modulesroom.server-miniLightweight serveropenssh, tailscale, firewallroom.serverFull serverdocker, nginx, postgresql, forgejo, vaultwarden, qemu-guestroom.containerContainer hostincus, distrobox","title":"Server Rooms","titles":["Rooms","Available Rooms"],"type":"section"},"13":{"category":"","href":"/rooms#desktop-rooms","subtitle":"","text":" RoomDescriptionKey Modulesroom.desktop.basisDesktop basedisplay manager, compositor (hyprland/niri/plasma), Catppuccin themingroom.desktop.generalFull desktopaudio (pipewire), input, fonts, apps (browser, mail, etc.)room.desktop.devDeveloper desktopIDEs (vscode/jetbrains), databases, dev-kit, containersroom.desktop.gameGaming desktopSteam, GPU drivers (AMD/NVIDIA), Wine, RetroArchroom.desktop.wslWSL desktopWSL-optimized desktop with GPU integration","title":"Desktop Rooms","titles":["Rooms","Available Rooms"],"type":"section"},"14":{"category":"","href":"/rooms#customizing-rooms","subtitle":"","text":" Rooms use lib.mkDefault for sub-module enables, so you can opt out of any individual module: cattery.room.desktop.game.enable = true;\n# Still get everything except JetBrains\ncattery.cli-apps.editor.jetbrains.enable = false;","title":"Customizing Rooms","titles":["Rooms"],"type":"section"},"15":{"category":"","href":"/modules#modules","subtitle":"","text":" Every module lives under the cattery namespace. Enable them individually or let rooms compose them for you.","title":"Modules","titles":[],"type":"page"},"16":{"category":"","href":"/modules#theming","subtitle":"","text":" ModuleDescriptionthemes.catppuccinCatppuccin color scheme for GTK, Qt, Hyprland, Plasma","title":"Theming","titles":["Modules","Module Categories"],"type":"section"},"17":{"category":"","href":"/modules#desktop","subtitle":"","text":" ModuleDescriptiondesktop.hyprlandHyprland Wayland compositordesktop.niriNiri scrollable-tiling compositordesktop.plasmaKDE Plasma desktopdesktop.gnomeGNOME desktopdesktop.addons.catppuccinCatppuccin for desktop addonsdesktop.addons.xdg-portalXDG Desktop Portal setup","title":"Desktop","ti